<subSubSection pageId="48" pageNumber="49" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="48.[151,1436,1081,1357]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,1189,1214]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Belizin" authorityYear="1952" box="[329,568,1189,1213]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Aspicera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simulacrum">
<emphasis box="[329,568,1189,1213]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Aspicera simulacrum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to the group of species with occiput and lateral margin of pronotum sharply carinate. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Belizin" authorityYear="1952" box="[342,505,1225,1249]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Aspicera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simulacrum">
<emphasis box="[342,505,1225,1249]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">A. simulacrum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ros-Farre" authorityYear="2013" box="[651,737,1225,1249]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Aspicera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="porif">
<emphasis box="[651,737,1225,1249]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">A. porif</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
having long and slender scutellar spine, scutellum convex and wing with long and dense marginal pubescence, but in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ros-Farre" authorityYear="2013" box="[766,851,1261,1285]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Aspicera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="porif">
<emphasis box="[766,851,1261,1285]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">A. porif</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
scutellar foveae are shallow and weakly sculptured, and scutellar disc is sharply convex, while in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Belizin" authorityYear="1952" box="[676,842,1297,1321]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Aspicera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simulacrum">
<emphasis box="[676,842,1297,1321]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">A. simulacrum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
scutellar foveae are deep and smooth, and scutellar disc is weakly convex.
</paragraph>
